[[File:AK47Figure54.jpg|thumb|AK-47 with Kalashnikov grenade launcher mounted to the muzzle]] [[File:RecznaWyrzytniaGranatowLzawiacych RWGL-3.jpg|thumb|RWGŁ-3 with Kalashnikov grenade launcher mounted to the muzzle]] [[File:RWGŁ-1 WPT 6 86.jpg|thumb|RWGŁ-1 with Kalashnikov grenade launcher mounted to the muzzle]]
All [[AK-47]] type rifles can mount a [[Rifle grenade#Cup-type|cup-type grenade-launcher]] that fires standard [[RGD-5]] Soviet hand-grenades. The soup-can shaped launcher is screwed onto the AK-47’s [[Muzzle (firearms)|muzzle]].<ref>https://www.ar15.com/content/webPDF/AK47USArmyOperatorManual.pdf</ref><ref>https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/AK-47_Operator%27s_Manual</ref> To fire, first insert a standard RGD-5 hand-grenade into the launcher and then remove the safety pin. Second, insert a special [[blank cartridge]] into the rifle's chamber. Third, place the butt-stock of the rifle on the ground and fire from this position.<ref>https://www.ar15.com/content/webPDF/AK47USArmyOperatorManual.pdf</ref> The maximum effective range is approximately 150 meters.<ref>https://www.ar15.com/content/webPDF/AK47USArmyOperatorManual.pdf</ref> This cup-type launcher can also be used to launch [[tear-gas]] and [[riot control]] grenades.
