{{Unreferenced|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}

'''OKFOL''' is an [[explosive]], used in a variety of applications. It is particularly suitable for use in [[shaped charge]]s. It normally consists of 95% [[HMX]] [[phlegmatized]] with 5% [[paraffin wax|wax]]. It has a density of 1.777&nbsp;grams per cubic centimetre and an [[explosive velocity]] of 8,670 metres per second.

==See also==
* [[Octol]], another HMX-based explosive.

